match.strDescriptionEN: Marseille failed to take advantage of PSG's missteps earlier in the season, and find themselves with only one point ahead of their hated Parisian rivals. Now the Villas-Boas team is called to make a result: will it succeed?

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-09-26 St Etienne vs Rennes
match.strDescriptionEN: With a start to the championship that is exceeding even the most optimistic expectations, Saint-Etienne after 4 games is leading the French top division together with Rennes. The two revelations collide to figure out who can be the real surprise of this season.

Only one victory in four games and a performance definitely not in line with the expectations of the beginning of the season. Bordeaux need to change course, and are hoping to do so against Nice, back from two consecutive KOs after their two initial victories.
Rudi Garcia's Lyon are looking for important points to get back into the title fight, in a championship in which the arch-rivals of Saint-Etienne are surprising everyone. How will it end in Lorient?

match.strEvent: Stade de Reims vs Paris SG
match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-09-27 Stade de Reims vs Paris SG
match.strDescriptionEN: The points lost in the very first days have led PSG to a vehement reaction, with two victories obtained in the last two league games. Now Tuchel's team wants to keep racing.

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-02 Paris SG vs Angers
match.strDescriptionEN: Seared by a slow start to the championship, PSG no longer wants to lose points on the road to reaffirm its dominance over French football. Angers arrives at the Parc des Princes, with Tuchel's team determined to close the case as soon as possible.

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-03 Lens vs St Etienne
match.strDescriptionEN: Excellent start to the season for the newly promoted Lens, who travels at an average of two points per game and managed to beat Paris Saint-Germain at home. Same average points for Saint-Etienne who are expected from an away game that is anything but trivial.

The start of the season was anything but perky for Vieira's Nice, who suffered a heavy 0-3 from Paris Saint-Germain in their last home game. Many difficulties also for Nantes, who have put together only one point in the last three days.

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-04 Rennes vs Stade de Reims

match.strDescriptionEN: Challenge between the greats of French football: Lyon hosts Marseille for a match that can decide the fate of the top league table.
First place in the standings and zero defeats so far for Rennes, where the young promise Camavinga shines. Opposite mood for Dijon, last, who scored only one point.

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-16 Nimes vs Paris SG

match.strDescriptionEN: 9 points for both but opposite trends before the break. While Bordeaux reversed the negative trend with a success, Marseille only won the opening match and are back from three consecutive draws.

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-17 Stade de Reims vs Lorient

match.strDescriptionEN: In the famous "Derby du Nord" of France, Lille and Lens compete in a highly anticipated match by the fans of both teams.

match.strVenue: Stade de la Beaujoire - Louis Fonteneau

match.strFilename: French Ligue 1 2020-10-18 St Etienne vs Nice
match.strDescriptionEN: Ten points each for Nice and Saint-Etienne, who compete against Geoffroy Gouchard. Vieira's team managed to regain victory on the last day, while the green-and-whites come from two consecutive defeats.

After their fantastic Champions League run in August, Lyon died at the start of the season with just seven points from their first six games. For Garcia, on the Strasbourg pitch, there are very heavy points at stake.
